Went to Guan Meimei's concert in Episode 28\n|| 28\n|-\n| [[Zheng Geping]] <br> \u90d1\u5404\u8bc4 || Bonnie\u7236\u4eb2||\n*Bonnie's father\n||29\n|-\n| [[Kenneth Chung (host)|Kenneth Chung]] <br> \u949f\u5764\u534e || Himself ||\n*Radio host\n|| 29\n|-\n| [[Somaline Ang]] <br> \u6d2a\u51cc || Herself ||\n*Actress\n||30\n|-\n| \u6d2a\u5049\u6587 || Mr Hong<br>\u6d2a\u7f16\u5267 || \n*Scriptwriter\n|| 30\n|}\n\n==Original Sound Track (OST) ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=center\n|-\n!style=\"background:#f2dfc6;\"| Song title\n!style=\"background:#f2dfc6;\"| Song type\n!style=\"background:#f2dfc6;\"| Lyrics\n!style=\"background:#f2dfc6;\"| Composer\n!style=\"background:#f2dfc6;\"| Performer\n!style=\"background:#f2dfc6;\"| Producer\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| The Extraordinary<br>\u683c\u5916\u7cbe\u5f69 \n|align=\"center\"| Opening theme song\n|align=\"center\"| \u738b\u632f\u58f0\n|align=\"center\"| \u5468\u4ee5\u529b\n|align=\"center\"| \u960e\u5955\u683c Janice Yan\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"|&mdash;\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Tears<br>\u501f\u4f60\u4e00\u70b9\u6cea\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| Sub-theme song \n|align=\"center\"| \u59da\u82e5\u9f99\n|align=\"center\"| \u90d1\u6960\n|align=\"center\"| \u52a8\u529b\u706b\u8f66 [[Power Station (Taiwanese band)|Power Station]]\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Wait For Love<br>\u7b49\u4e00\u7b49\u7231\u60c5\n|align=\"center\"| \u4e50\u58f0\n|align=\"center\"| \u9093\u78a7\u6e90\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| \u7f57\u7f8e\u4eea [[Bonnie Loo]]\n|rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| \u9ea6\u5982\u4e3d\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Watching Over You<br>\u5b88\u62a4\u4f60\n|align=\"center\"| \u9ad8\u98de\n|align=\"center\"| Benny Wong\n|}\n\n==Development==\n\nDakota Crescent is one of Singapore's earliest [[Housing and Development Board|(HDB)]] estates, built in 1958 by the [[Singapore Improvement Trust]] (SIT), which preceded the HDB. In July 2014, it was decided that the housing estate would be redeveloped under the HDB's [[Selective En bloc Redevelopment Scheme|SERS]] scheme and all residents would have to relocate by 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Dakota Crescent tenants hit by news of redevelopment|url=http://www.todayonline.com/singapore/dakota-crescent-tenants-hit-news-redevelopment| access-date= 13 December 2016}}</ref> This prompted a campaign by activists for its conservation,<ref>{{cite news|title=\"Group pushing to save Dakota Crescent\"|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/group-pushing-to-save-dakota-crescent|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref> works of art to be created about it<ref>{{cite news|title=Community theatre show puts spotlight on Dakota Crescent and its residents|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/entertainment/community-theatre-show/2915036.html?cx_tag=similarcna&cid=tg:recos:similarcna:standard#cxrecs_s|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Overwhelming response to Drama Box\u2019s site-specific performance in Dakota Crescent|url=http://www.todayonline.com/entertainment/arts/overwhelming-response-drama-boxs-site-specific-performance-dakota-crescent?cx_tag=similartd&cid=tg:recos:similartd:standard#cxrecs_s|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref> and also a spike in the amount of coverage given to Dakota Crescent by the media.<ref>{{cite news|title=5 things to remember about Dakota Crescent|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/5-things-to-remember-about-dakota-crescent|accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref> Within weeks of the announcement by the HDB, Dakota Crescent drew considerable attention from many Singaporeans, amid which this drama series was produced.\n\nThis drama series was produced also as a means of kick-starting the commemoration of 35 years of Singapore-produced Chinese-language television in Singapore. As part of this, Mediacorp's famous Chinese-speaking comedy icons, such as ''[[Paris and Milan]]'' character Auntie Lucy (played by [[Dennis Chew]]) and Liang Po Po (played by [[Jack Neo]]) of ''Comedy Nite'', will be making cameo appearances in this drama.<ref>{{cite news|title=\"\u7eda\u8000\"\u5496\u5561\u9986\u6084\u6084\u5f00\u4e1a \u5218\u5b50\u7eda\u300a\u5927\u82f1\u96c4\u300b\u9996\u6b21\u6311\u6218\u641e\u7b11\u89d2\u8272|url=http://www.channel8news.sg/news8/lifestyle/entertainment/20160526-lif-jesseca/2819006.html?cid=ch8news-fb|publisher=Channel 8 News and Current Affairs|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=14 June 2016|language=Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u9648\u6cd3\u5b87\uff1a\u65b0\u5267\u89d2\u8272\u53d6\u540d\u81ea\"\u8fbe\u54e5\u6253\u5f2f\"\u611f\u8363\u5e78 \u62cd\u5b8c\u620f\u6025\u7740\u56de\u5bb6\u770b\u5b69\u5b50|url=http://www.channel8news.sg/news8/lifestyle/entertainment/20160526-lif-shaun/2820150.html|publisher=Channel 8 News and Current Affairs|date=26 May 2016|accessdate=14 June 2016|language=Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Auntie Lucy\u91cd\u51fa\u6c5f\u6e56 \u5ba2\u4e32\u91cd\u5934\u5267\u300a\u5927\u82f1\u96c4\u300b|url=http://www.channel8news.sg/news8/lifestyle/entertainment/20160527-lif-lucy/2820556.html|publisher=Channel 8 News and Current Affairs|date=27 May 2016|accessdate=14 June 2016|language=Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u9648\u6c49\u73ae\u633a\u810a\u67f1\u9aa8\u4f24\u53e3\u62cd\u620f \u4e3a\u6bcd\u4eb2\u7948\u798f\u6539\u5403\u7d20|url=http://www.channel8news.sg/news8/lifestyle/entertainment/20160527-lif-hanwei/2820558.html|publisher=Channel 8 News and Current Affairs|date=27 May 2016|accessdate=14 June 2016|language=Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u6881\u5a46\u5a46\u91cd\u51fa\u6c5f\u6e56 \u6881\u5fd7\u5f3a\u65b0\u7247\u62d2\u5f53\u5bfc\u6f14\uff1f|url=http://tv.toggle.sg/en/channel8/entnews/default-6388454|publisher=Toggle|date=11 June 2016|accessdate=14 June 2016|language=Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u90d1\u658c\u8f89\u8d74\u4e2d\u56fd\u6f14\u8499\u53e4\u5927\u6c57 \u9648\u6cd3\u5b87\u4e0e\u59bb\u5973\u5206\u623f\u7761|url=http://tv.toggle.sg/en/channel8/entnews/default-6403322#slideshow-1|publisher=Toggle|date=18 June 2016|lang