rom 29 November 2016 to 9 January 2017.\n\n==Awards & Nominations==\n===[[Star Awards 2017]]===\nThe series has the most nominations in [[Star Awards 2017]], and won two, which was Best Supporting Actress and Drama Serial.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\" - style=\"background:#FAEB86;\" align=\"center\" | [[Star Awards]] \u2013 Acting Awards\n|-\n! Accolades !! Category !! Nominees !! Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|The Road to Star Awards 2017 Episode 1<br> \u7ea2\u661f\u5927\u5956 \u5f71\u805a\u54cd\u5bb4\n| [[Star Awards for Best Director|Best Director]] <br> \u6700\u4f73\u5bfc\u6f14\n| Wong Foong Hwee <br> \u9ec4\u82ac\u83f2\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Star Awards for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]] <br> \u6700\u4f73\u5267\u672c\n| Ang Eng Tee <br> \u6d2a\u8363\u72c4\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|The Road to Star Awards 2017 Episode 2 <br> \u7ea2\u661f\u5927\u5956 \u5f71\u805a\u54cd\u5bb4\n| [[Star Awards for London Choco Roll Happiness Award|London Choco Roll Happiness Award]] <br> \u6700\u4f73\u5f00\u5fc3\u679c\u5956\n| [[Shaun Chen]] <br> \u9648\u6cd3\u5b87\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Bioskin Healthiest Hair Award\n| [[Desmond Ng]] <br> \u9ec4\u632f\u9686\n| {{nom}} \n|-\n|rowspan=\"10\"| [[Star Awards 2017]] Awards Ceremony \u7ea2\u661f\u5927\u59562017\u9881\u5956\u793c\n|  [[Star Awards for Best Actor|Best Actor]] <br> \u6700\u4f73\u7537\u4e3b\u89d2\n| [[Shaun Chen]] <br> \u9648\u6cd3\u5b87\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Star Awards for Best Actress|Best Actress]]<br> \u6700\u4f73\u5973\u4e3b\u89d2\n| [[Jesseca Liu]] <br> \u5218\u5b50\u7eda\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]] <br> \u6700\u4f73\u7537\u914d\u89d2\n| [[Andie Chen]] <br> \u9648\u90a6\u92c6\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"| [[Star Awards for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]  <br> \u6700\u4f73\u5973\u914d\u89d2\n| [[Paige Chua]] <br> \u8521\u7426\u6167\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Pan Lingling]] <br> \u6f58\u73b2\u73b2\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Bonnie Loo]] <br> \u7f57\u7f8e\u4eea\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Aileen Tan]] <br> \u9648\u4e3d\u8d1e\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| [[Star Awards for Best Evergreen Artiste Award|Best Evergreen Artiste Award]] <br> \u5e38\u9752\u6f14\u7ece\u5956\n| {{Nom}}\n|-\n|  [[Star Awards for Best Drama Serial|Best Drama Serial]]  <br> \u6700\u4f73\u7535\u89c6\u5267\n| {{N/A}} \n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of MediaCorp Channel 8 Chinese drama series (2010s)]]\n* [[List of Hero episodes]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{sequence\n|prev=''[[The Dream Makers II|The Dream Makers]]'' (season 2)<br />[[Star Awards 2016|2015-16]]\n|list=[[Star Awards for Best Drama Serial|''Star Awards'' for Best Drama Serial]]<br />''Hero''<br />[[Star Awards 2017|2016-17]]\n|next=''[[When Duty Calls]]''<br />[[Star Awards 2018|2017-18]]\n}}\n\n{{Star Awards for Best Drama Serial}}\n\n[[Category:Singapore Chinese dramas]]\n[[Category:2016 Singaporean television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 Singaporean television series endings]]\n[[Category:Channel 8 (Singapore) shows]]\n", "name_user": "116.87.56.222", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eZhou (Fada) family)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hero_(2016_TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "Bierstadt", "text_new": "{{other uses}}\n{{Infobox German location\n|name          = Bierstadt\n|name_local    = \n|image_photo    = \n|image_caption  = \n|type           = Borough\n|City        = Wiesbaden\n|image_coa      = Wappen Wiesbaden-Bierstadt.svg\n|coordinates    = {{coord|50|05|00|N|8|17|00|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|state         = Hesse\n|district  = urban\n|borough       =\n|divisions   = \n|B\u00fcrgermeistertitel    = Mayor of Borough\n|mayor = Reinhold Hepp \n|party = CDU\n|area           = 9.22\n|population     = 12304\n|population_as_of       = 30.06.2008\n|postal_code    = 65191\n|area_code      = 0611\n|licence  =\n|plantext = Location of Bierstadt in Wiesbaden\n|image_plan     = Wiesbaden Karte Bierstadt.PNG\n}}\n'''Bierstadt''' is a [[borough]] of the city of [[Wiesbaden]], capital of the state of [[Hesse]], [[Germany]]. The district is located in the eastern part of the city, directly east of downtown Wiesbaden, and has about 12,300 inhabitants.  Formerly an independent municipality, the town was incorporated into Wiesbaden on April 1, 1928. While ''Bierstadt'' can be translated ''Beer Town'', the name is actually derived from [[Saint Brigid of Kildare]], Ireland (''Birgid'' in German).\n\n==History==\n[[Image:Nikolauskirche WB.jpg|thumb|left|Church of St. Nicholas, Bierstadt|200px]]\nThe earliest traces of settlement in the Bierstadt area date to the [[Stone Age]]. However, Bierstadt was first mentioned in historical records, as \"Birgidestad\", in a deed of gift on March 12, 927. The town was founded by Irish monks, who named it after the Irish national saint, St. Brigid. In the 11th\u201312th centuries, the (now Protestant) Church of St. Nicholas was built. The church is not only the oldest existing church in Wiesbaden, but, after the Roman-era Heathens' Wall in downtown Wiesbaden, is the second oldest building of any kind in the city.\n\nIn the [[Middle Ages]], Bierstadt came under the dominion of [[Nassau (state)|Nassau]], but was subject to strong influences from the [[Archdiocese of Mainz]]. In the wake of the Reformation, Bierstadt came fully under the control of Nassau.\n\nAfter the [[Thirty Years' War]], the town had only 17 inhabitants. Efforts at reconstruction were set back through a fire in 1691. By the middle of the 18th century, Bierstadt had about 500 residents.\n\nThe remains of a medieval watchtower, the  ''Bierstadter Warte'', are located on a height between Wiesbaden and the district. The Warte is now part of the coat of arms.\nIn 1898, a large observation tower, the [[Wiesbaden Bismarck Tower]], was planned to be built at this site. A temporary wooden tower was constructed in 1910, but funding for the permanent structure could not be obtained. The temporary tower was demolished in 1918.\n\nDuring the [[Third Reich]], Nazism dominated in Bierstadt. On November 9, 1938, the Bierstadt synagogue, dating to 1827, was destroyed.\n\nAfter [[World War II]], about 1800 homes were built in Bierstadt for occupation forces of the [[United States Army]]. The Aukamm and Crestview developments are located on the northwest and west side of Bierstadt, respectively.\n\n==Infrastructure==\nBierstadt has a library and two schools, including one primary school - Grundschule Bierstadt, and  a gymnasium named Theodor-Fliedner-Schule which was formerly a middle school. Bierstadt is next to the ''Aukammtal'' and has access to the German Federal Route 455.\n\nBierstadt has two churches. In addition to the Protestant church (formerly the church of St. Nicholas), there is the [[Roman Catholic]] church of St. Birgid.\n\n==Twinning==\nSince 1991, Bierstadt has had a partnership with the [[France|French]] commune of [[Terrasson-Lavilledieu]]. The town of Terrasson is located on the banks of the [[V\u00e9z\u00e8re]] in southwestern France, about 150&nbsp;km east of [[Bordeaux]] in the heart of [[Aquitaine]], with which Hesse maintains a regional partnership.\n\n== Sources ==\n* adapted from [[:de:Wiesbaden-Bierstadt|German Wikipedia]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://centennial.legion.org/france/postgr07 Post GR07] at American Legion Centennial Celebration (centennial.legion.org)\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20041226015846/http://www.wiesbaden.de/leben_wi/stadtteile/bierstadt.php (in German)\n*http://www.marlionetta.de\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20030801182401/http://www.fc34bierstadt.de/\n*http://www.kornmayer.com\n\n{{Wiesbaden}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Boroughs of Wiesbaden]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses}}\n{{Infobox German location\n|name          = Bierstadt\n|name_local    = \n|image_photo    = \n|image_caption  = \n|of_city_coa    =Wappen_Wiesbaden.svg\n|type           = Borough\n|article_       = of\n|City        = Wiesbaden\n|Town        = \n|image_coa      = Wappen Wiesbaden-Bierstadt.svg\n|map_           = Karte Wiesbaden in Deutschland.png\n|map_cap        = \n|coordinates    = {{coord|50|05|00|N|8|17|00|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|state         = Hesse\n|district  = urban\n|borough       =\n|divisions   = \n|_office        = Poststra\u00dfe 11A<br>65191 Wiesbaden-<br>Bierstadt\n|B\u00fcrgermeistertitel    = Mayor of Borough\n|mayor = Reinhold Hepp ([[Christian Democratic Union (Germany)|CDU]])\n|area           = 9.22\n|population     = 12304\n|population_as_of       = 30.06.2008\n|pop_ref       = \n|postal_code    = 65191\n|area_code      = 0611\n|licence  =\n|free_2         = Annexation date\n|free_2_txt     = 1 April 1928\n|year         = \n|plantext = Location of Bierstadt in Wiesbaden\n|image_plan     = Wiesbaden Karte Bierstadt.PNG|100px\n}}\n'''Bierstadt''' is a [[borough]] of the city of [[Wiesbaden]], capital of the state of [[Hesse]], [[Germany]]. The district is located in the eastern part of the city, directly east of downtown Wiesbaden, and has about 12,300 inhabitants.  Formerly an independent municipality, the town was incorporated into Wiesbaden on April 1, 1928. While ''Bierstadt'' can be translated ''Beer Town'', the name is actually derived from [[Saint Brigid of Kildare]], Ireland (''Birgid'' in German).\n\n==History==\n[[Image:Nikolauskirche WB.jpg|thumb|left|Church of St. Nicholas, Bierstadt|200px]]\nThe earliest traces of settlement in the Bierstadt area date to the [[Stone Age]]. However, Bierstadt was first mentioned in historical records, as \"Birgidestad\", in a deed of gift on March 12, 927. The town was founded by Irish monks, who named it after the Irish national saint, St. Brigid. In the 11th\u201312th centuries, the (now Protestant) Church of St. Nicholas was built. The church is not only the oldest existing church in Wiesbaden, but, after the Roman-era Heathens' Wall in downtown Wiesbaden, is the second oldest building of any kind in the city.\n\nIn the [[Middle Ages]], Bierstadt came under the dominion of [[Nassau (state)|Nassau]], but was subject to strong influences from the [[Archdiocese of Mainz]]. In the wake of the Reformation, Bierstadt came fully under the control of Nassau.\n\nAfter the [[Thirty Years' War]], the town had only 17 inhabitants. Efforts at reconstruction were set back through a fire in 1691. By the middle of the 18th century, Bierstadt had about 500 residents.\n\nThe remains of a medieval watchtower, the  ''Bierstadter Warte'', are located on a height between Wiesbaden and the district. The Warte is now part of the coat of arms.\nIn 1898, a large observation tower, the [[Wiesbaden Bismarck Tower]], was planned to be built at this site. A temporary wooden tower was constructed in 1910, but funding for the permanent structure could not be obtained. The temporary tower was demolished in 1918.\n\nDuring the [[Third Reich]], Nazism dominated in Bierstadt. On November 9, 1938, the Bierstadt synagogue, dating to 1827, was destroyed.\n\nAfter [[World War II]], about 1800 homes were built in Bierstadt for occupation forces of the [[United States Army]]. The Aukamm and Crestview developments are located on the northwest and west side of Bierstadt, respectively.\n\n==Infrastructure==\nBierstadt has a library and two schools, including one primary school - Grundschule Bierstadt, and  a gymnasium named Theodor-Fliedner-Schule which was formerly a middle school. Bierstadt is next to the ''Aukammtal'' and has access to the German Federal Route 455.\n\nBierstadt has two churches. In addition to the Protestant church (formerly the church of St. Nicholas), there is the [[Roman Catholic]] church of St. Birgid.\n\n==Twinning==\nSince 1991, Bierstadt has had a partnership with the [[France|French]] commune of [[Terrasson-Lavilledieu]]. The town of Terrasson is located on the banks of the [[V\u00e9z\u00e8re]] in southwestern France, about 150&nbsp;km east of [[Bordeaux]] in the heart of [[Aquitaine]], with which Hesse maintains a regional partnership.\n\n== Sources ==\n* adapted from [[:de:Wiesbaden-Bierstadt|German Wikipedia]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://centennial.legion.org/france/postgr07 Post GR07] at American Legion Centennial Celebration (centennial.legion.org)\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20041226015846/http://www.wiesbaden.de/leben_wi/stadtteile/bierstadt.php (in German)\n*http://www.marlionetta.de\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20030801182401/http://www.fc34bierstadt.de/\n*http://www.kornmayer.com\n\n{{Wiesbaden}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Boroughs of Wiesbaden]]\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bierstadt"}
